> **⚠️ IMPORTANT:** Open the Heroic Games once before continuing! This generates the folders we need to use.

## Heroic Games 

Will add part talking about Heroic install post recording.
### Download the Wine Runner

Press this link to download the wine runner we need here or from the releases link below.

[Reccomended wine here](https://dawn.wine/NelloKudo/wine-miniloader/releases/download/wine-miniloader-tkg-11.0-1/wine-tkg-miniloader-staging-fonts-11.0-1-x86_64.tar.xz)


Can download different builds/releases from [here](https://dawn.wine/NelloKudo/wine-miniloader/releases) but I will be recommending the one above mainly for compability with Heroic flatpak when it comes to video playback.



### Extracting the Archive

After downloading, extract the `tar.xz` file into the appropriate directory for your runner.

| Runner | Flatpak location (default) | Native (Non‑Flatpak) location |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Heroic** | `$HOME/.var/app/com.heroicgameslauncher.hgl/config/heroic/tools/wine/` | `$HOME/.config/heroic/tools/wine/` |


**One line command  if you downloaded the reccommended tar.xz to Downloads folder**



**Flatpak version of Heroic:**
```bash
tar -xvf ~/Downloads/wine-tkg-miniloader-staging-fonts-11.0-1-x86_64.tar.xz -C $HOME/.var/app/com.heroicgameslauncher.hgl/config/heroic/tools/wine/
```
**Native version of Heroic:**
```bash
tar -xvf ~/Downloads/wine-tkg-miniloader-staging-fonts-11.0-1-x86_64.tar.xz -C $HOME/.config/heroic/tools/wine/
```
Alternative GUI Method: If you don't want to use the terminal, simply extract the file in your File Explorer and copy the resulting folder into whichever Heroic path (Flatpak or Native) applies to you.




Next, download the latest .exe installer directly from the game's official website and save it to your Downloads folder and we can move onto Heroic Games Launcher

